## 🚀 **PCIS: Phoenix Container Integration System**
**Architecture**: Local-first development with comprehensive testing via Claude AI agents and TPS methodology
**Components**: `lib/pcis/local_first/` (rules, session_state, database, volumes), validation/monitoring systems, hybrid Ubuntu+NixOS architecture
**Rules**: Relative data paths, no external mounts, local DB directories, project-only storage, zero tolerance enforcement
**Testing**: 1 supervisor + 4 workers + 5 support agents across unit/integration/performance/scalability/load testing (100%/95%/80%/75%/70% coverage targets)
**Commands**: `elixir scripts/pcis/development_workflow.exs --interactive`, `elixir scripts/pcis/validation_cli.exs --all`, PHICS integration mandatory
**Success**: 20+ modules, 100% local-first compliance, enterprise-grade testing, real-time monitoring, production-ready infrastructure
**Mandatory**: PCIS validation before commits, testing framework only, session management, local-first compliance, PHICS containers, hot-reloading validation

